 Prophet T B Joshua, the founder of The Synagogue, Church Of All Nations (SCOAN), died in Lagos on Saturday evening shortly after concluding a programme at his church, According to the family sources whose name withheld said an official statement was still being prepared. Prophet T B Joshua was 57, cause of death yet to be disclosed, but family sources confirmed that his remains had been deposited at the morgue and an autopsy would be performed forthwith. More details shortly <img loading="lazy" class="alignnone  wp-image-9259" src="https://i1.wp.com/mlpthjcvvzze.i.optimole.com/l57LFPo.2zvi~5f0f9/w:auto/h:auto/q:90/https://i0.wp.com/ebitu.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Screenshot-2021-05-05-at-1.47.18-AM.png?resize=87%2C27&#038;ssl=1" alt="EBITU | #EbituBlog" width="87" height="27" data-recalc-dims="1" data-recalc-dims="1"> The post BREAKING: Prophet T B Joshua is dead appeared first on E B I T U™. Late Ada Jesus: You’ll Be Next, Rita Edochie Warns CriticsMay 31, 2021In "Entertainment" King to leave Everton after six-month dealJune 4, 2021In "Sports" #EndSARS: Pathologist presents bodies of 99 protesters killed in Lekki, other parts of LagosJune 6, 2021In "Slider 1"